Source: webcleaner
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.5.6.1
Build-Depends: python2.2-dev, debhelper (>= 3.0.0), debconf

Package: webcleaner
Architecture: any
Depends: python (>= 2.2), python2.2-xmlbase, debconf, python-dns
Conflicts: python (>= 2.3)
Suggests: webcleanertools, python2.2-tarfile
Description: a filtering HTTP proxy
 Features:
  o disable animated GIFs
  o compress documents on-the-fly (with gzip)
  o remove/add HTTP headers
  o remove unwanted HTML (adverts, javascript, ...)
  o customizable to suit your (filtering) needs
  o HTTP/1.1 support

Package: webcleanertools
Section: x11
Architecture: all
Depends: fxpy-python2.2 (>= 1.0.0), python (>= 2.2), webcleaner
Conflicts: python (>= 2.3)
Description: configuration and visualization tools for webcleaner
 webcleanerconf is a nice GUI configuration tool for the WebCleaner proxy.
 wcheaders is a graphical interface to display the HTTP headers
 of all requests the local WebCleaner proxy handles.

